{
  "stem": "21008.2",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Everyone-- everyone was Jewish, the whole apartment building.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, yes, yes.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They were all Jewish families.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, no, no.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That-- there were Jewish houses in-between.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But of course, after '38, after the Kristallnacht, you had no Jewish stores anymore anyway, you know.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So the surroundings were not Jewish.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I can't say that.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Right, and as much as I can assume that those were buildings belonging originally to Jews, that they were owned by Jews, you know.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And that's probably how it came that they designated these houses as Jew houses.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In April of '39.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "April of '39, and now, I could walk to school, which was nice.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I remember-- I remember only one boy were able-- left my class.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Of course, within the school were probably more.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But in my class, only one boy was able to go to America in '39.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "That I remember.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "None of the teachers left.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "None of the teachers.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It was very hard to get out.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was a Sunday, September 1, 1939.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we had a radio, and we heard that Germany had invaded Poland.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And my father's reaction was that's the end of Hitler.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "If he goes into a war, he will go kaput.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He hoped that he would go kaput fast, but, of course, that didn't happen.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Yeah, that's how we heard it.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I think pretty soon after war-- the war started, ration cards were issued for all, for all the population.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And-- and in the beginning, I think the first cards we got were the same as all the Germans got.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But then the second set already had a J stamped on-- 'Jew.' And, oh, god, there were so many restrictions, you know.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Then it-- after Kristallnacht, one restriction after the other.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
